      <section eId="sec_CHC-1025-2">
        <num>CHC 1025.2</num>
        <heading>1025.2.  Stipulation; consent to judgment; resident, nonresident parents</heading>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1025-2__subsec_1">
          <num>(1)</num>
          <content>
            <p>He personally appears before the court.  A parent who resides either in another parish or in another state may personally appear before the court exercising juvenile court jurisdiction in his place of residence.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1025-2__subsec_2">
          <num>(2)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The court fully informs him of his rights and the consequences of such a stipulation.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1025-2__subsec_3">
          <num>(3)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The parent knowingly and voluntarily consents to the judgment.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=72553</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
